    <p>LON­DON • Slaven Bilic ad­mit­ted he was hugely dis­ap­pointed at be­ing sacked by West Bromwich Al­bion but said he left the Pre­mier League club with his “head held high”.</p>
    <p>In an in­ter­view with The Daily Mail, the Croat added he was “sad that it hasn’t worked out in the way we wanted”.</p>
    <p>Sam Al­lardyce has re­placed him on an 18-month deal, with the Bag­gies sec­ond from bottom on seven points.</p>


